{
    "name": "Giant Jellyfish",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Giant Jellyfish",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Unlike its smaller cousins, the giant jellyfish is an active predator that chases down its prey through reefs or open water. It can even squeeze its enormous bell-shaped body into the tight confines of shipwrecks to drape its mane of tentacles across the exposed flesh of its prey.",
